Description . COLOR . Body more or less uniformly dark reddish-brown to black dorsally, elytron with one small, preapical, pale spot on intervals 5–8 or 6–8 ; antennomere 1 brown dorsally, antennomere 2 (except on basal half in many specimens), 3 and 4 (except on apical half in some specimens) paler, yellow to reddishyellow, antennomeres 5–7 and ( 10 )– 11 dark brown to brownish-black, antennomeres 8 and 9 and in most specimens part or all of antennomere 10 whitish; femur yellow on basal half or so, brown on apical half or so, tibia brown with pale yellow submedian band. MICROSCULPTURE. Body without meshes or microlines dorsally. HEAD . Posterior supraorbital seta located at about level of posterior edge of eye. PROTHORAX. Pronotum without distinct transverse wrinkles; side with one seta. Tergosternal suture distinct over entire length of pronotum. ELYTRA. Interval 3 with four to seven discal setae, interval 5 with one to four discal setae, interval 7 without setae. Strial punctures moderately coarse on striae 3–5 on basal half, fine to very fine on remaining striae. Interval 3 , or 3 and 4 , with shallow depression before middle of elytra; intervals 7 and 8 without or with faint preapical swelling. ABDOMEN. Sterna with sparse pubescence. MALE GENITALIA. Median lobe as illustrated (
Fig. 16
).

Geographical distribution . This species ranges from southeastern Arizona south at least to Honduras (
Fig. 21
).
